As a young man I worked as a fire scout and I believe fires can be better extinguished by fighting fires from inside the burned out area Directing water hoses from the inside , would be much more efficient as the OVERFLOW 75% of the water sprayed goes towards wetting the unburned bush. The reverse is hosing from outside the circle, 75% of the water is totally wasted in wetting the already burned out  bush. Fighting from the backside is much more effective and would cut down the firewall much more quickly.
